Boil a #kettle{} fully.

Pour it into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Boil the @spaghetti{180%grams}, ~{8%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through.

Meanwhile, heat a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Fry the @diced chorizo{60%grams}, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in the @tomato puree{30%grams}. Fry, ~{1%minute}.

Add the @creme fraiche{150%grams}, @chicken stock paste{10%grams}, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @water{150%milliliters} for the sauce. Simmer, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the @baby spinach{40%grams} in handfuls, making sure it's piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir the pasta into the sauce. Add a splash of water if needed.

Share between #bowls{}. Crumble over the @Greek style salad cheese{50%grams}.

Sprinkle over the @crispy onions{1%sachet} and @chilli flakes{1%pinch}.

Enjoy!